---
layout: base
title: "Suggest a Song"
description: Know a song whose lyrics reflect freethought, humanist, or rationalist ideas? Tell us about it and we'll review it for inclusion.
permalink: /music/submit/
---

<div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-20);">
  <div class="container--prose">

    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="breadcrumbs__list">
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/projects/">Projects</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/music/">Freethought Music</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/music/songs/">Songs</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item breadcrumbs__item--current" aria-current="page">Suggest a Song</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--space-8); padding-bottom: var(--space-6); border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-ink);">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.16em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">Freethought Music</p>
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-masthead); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3.815rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Suggest a song</h1>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ink-muted); line-height: var(--leading-loose); max-width: 62ch; margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
        If you know a song whose lyrics reflect freethought, humanist, or rationalist ideas &mdash; questioning faith, celebrating reason, defending human dignity &mdash; we want to hear about it.
      </p>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink-faint); max-width: 62ch;">
        Looking for a playlist instead? <a href="/music/playlists/submit/" style="color: var(--color-link);">Suggest a playlist &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">

      <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
        <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--color-ink); padding-bottom: var(--space-2); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-ink);">What we're looking for</h2>
        <ul style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--text-base); color: var(--color-ink-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); padding-left: var(--space-5); margin-bottom: 0;">
          <li><strong>Lyrics over vibes.</strong> The words should reflect a freethought, humanist, or rationalist idea &mdash; not just a song that "feels" secular.</li>
          <li><strong>On YouTube.</strong> We embed with YouTube's IFrame API. If it isn't on YouTube, we can't play it on-site.</li>
          <li><strong>Any era, any genre.</strong> Folk, metal, classical, hip-hop, pop &mdash; all welcome. Protest songs from the 1960s sit next to indie rock from last year.</li>
          <li><strong>One song per submission.</strong> If you have a whole batch, please submit them one at a time so we can track each.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <form action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit" method="POST" class="w3f" style="margin: var(--space-6) 0;">
        <input type="hidden" name="access_key" value="{{ site.forms.accessKey }}">
        <input type="hidden" name="subject" value="Song suggestion, {{ site.title }}">
        <input type="hidden" name="redirect" value="{{ site.url }}/thank-you/">
        <input type="hidden" name="from_name" value="{{ site.title }} Music Form">
        <input type="checkbox" name="botcheck" class="visually-hidden" style="display:none" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off">

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-url">YouTube link <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
          <input class="w3f__input" type="url" name="song_url" id="mu-url" required aria-required="true" placeholder="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=...">
          <p class="w3f__hint">Paste the full YouTube watch URL. <code>youtu.be/</code> short links and <code>/embed/</code> URLs are also fine.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__row">
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-title">Song title <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="title" id="mu-title" required aria-required="true" placeholder="Imagine">
          </div>
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-artist">Artist <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="artist" id="mu-artist" required aria-required="true" placeholder="John Lennon">
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__row">
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-album">Album <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="album" id="mu-album" placeholder="Imagine">
          </div>
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-year">Release year <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="number" name="year" id="mu-year" min="1800" max="2100" placeholder="1971">
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-genre">Genre <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
          <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="genre" id="mu-genre" placeholder="Folk Rock, Indie Pop, Classical&hellip;">
          <p class="w3f__hint">Your best guess is fine. We normalize genres on our end.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-tags">Themes / tags <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
          <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="tags" id="mu-tags" placeholder="humanism, religion, reason, freedom">
          <p class="w3f__hint">Comma-separated. Examples: <em>humanism, religion, reason, freedom, science, doubt, war, peace</em>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="w3f__group">
          <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-why">Why this song fits freethought <span class="w3f__required">*</span></label>
          <textarea class="w3f__textarea" name="reason" id="mu-why" rows="4" maxlength="1200" required aria-required="true" placeholder="Point to a specific lyric or theme. E.g.: 'The chorus &ldquo;above us only sky&rdquo; is a direct rejection of religious cosmology&hellip;'"></textarea>
          <p class="w3f__hint">A line or two is plenty. We just want to see you've actually listened.</p>
        </div>

        <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule); margin: var(--space-6) 0;">

        <div class="w3f__row">
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-sname">Your name <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="text" name="submitter_name" id="mu-sname" autocomplete="name">
          </div>
          <div class="w3f__group">
            <label class="w3f__label" for="mu-email">Email <span class="w3f__optional">(optional)</span></label>
            <input class="w3f__input" type="email" name="email" id="mu-email" autocomplete="email" placeholder="only if you'd like a reply">
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="w3f__fineprint" style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-ink-faint); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); max-width: 62ch; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
          We review every suggestion before adding it. Not every song makes it in &mdash; we're looking for <em>lyrics</em> that reflect freethought, not just an artist's biography. You'll only hear from us if we have a question.
        </p>

        <button type="submit" class="w3f__submit">Submit song</button>
      </form>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
